me?.trim() || agent.provider),"," \t\t\ticon: this.iconForAgentProvider(agent.provider) ?? this.icon,"," \t\t}));"],"additions":4,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"src/vs/sessions/services/sessions/common/session.ts","lines":["@@ -19,6 +19,15 @@ export interface ISessionType {"," \treadonly label: string;"," \t/** Icon for this session type. */"," \treadonly icon: ThemeIcon;","+\t/**","+\t * The workbench chat session type (contribution id) this session type maps","+\t * to, when it differs from {@link id}. Agent-host providers use a bare agent","+\t * provider name as {@link id} (e.g. `claude`) but register their chat session","+\t * contribution and models under `agent-host-<provider>`, so they set this to","+\t * bridge the two (e.g. for entitlement/model availability lookups). Defaults","+\t * to {@link id} when omitted.","+\t */","+\treadonly chatSessionType?: string;"," }"," "," export const GITHUB_REMOTE_FILE_SCHEME = 'github-remote-file';"],"additions":9,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/agentSessions/sessionTypeAvailability.ts","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,148 @@","+/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------","+ *  Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation. All rights reserved.","+ *  Licensed under the MIT License. See License.txt in the project root for license information.","+ *--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/","+","+import { IMarkdownString, MarkdownString } from '../../../../../base/common/htmlContent.js';","+import { localize } from '../../../../../nls.js';","+import { ChatEntitlement, IChatEntitlementService } from '../../../../services/chat/common/chatEntitlementService.js';","+import { IChatSessionsService } from '../../common/chatSessionsService.js';","+import { ILanguageModelsService } from '../../common/languageModels.js';","+import { hasModelsTargetingSession } from '../widget/input/chatModelSelectionLogic.js';","+","+/**","+ * Why a session type cannot currently be selected, or","+ * {@link SessionTypeAvailability.Available} when it can.","+ */","+export enum SessionTypeAvailability {","+\t/** Selectable — has an Auto fallback or at least one targeted/BYOK model. */","+\tAvailable,","+\t/** Unusable, but the user can resolve it by upgrading (Copilot Free / Student). */","+\tUpgradeRequired,","+\t/** Unusable with no upgrade path — no models target it and the user is already on a paid plan. */","+\tNoModels,","+}","+","+/**","+ * Whether the given session type can currently produce a request, and if not,","+ * why. A session type is usable when it can fall back to the synthetic \"Auto\"","+ * model ({@link IChatSessionsService.supportsAutoModelForSessionType}) or has at","+ * least one model targeting it (e.g. a user-configured BYOK model). A type that","+ * does not require its own models ({@link IChatSessionsService.requiresCustomModelsForSessionType})","+ * — e.g. the cloud delegation agent, which runs remotely without a local model —","+ * also stays usable on a paid plan even with neither an Auto fallback nor a","+ * targeted model. When a type is not usable, Copilot Free / Student (EDU) users","+ * see an Upgrade affordance ({@link SessionTypeAvailability.UpgradeRequired});","+ * paid users whose type genuinely requires its own models but has none simply","+ * have no models ({@link SessionTypeAvailability.NoModels}) and are shown an","+ * explanation with no upgrade button. Unavailable types are greyed out in the","+ * picker either way.","+ *","+ * While the type's contribution isn't registered yet (e.g. during a window","+ * reload before the extension host re-registers), this returns","+ * {@link SessionTypeAvailability.Available} so a harness is never locked","+ * prematurely; the model picker is the backstop and shows \"No models available\"","+ * for an active session in that window.","+ *","+ * Shared by the chat input session-type picker and the Agents window harness","+ * picker so both surfaces apply the same rule.","+ */","+export function getSessionTypeAvailability(","+\tchatSessionsService: IChatSessionsService,","+\tchatEntitlementService: IChatEntitlementService,","+\tlanguageModelsService: ILanguageModelsService,","+\ttype: string,","+): SessionTypeAvailability {","+\tif (chatSessionsService.supportsAutoModelForSessionType(type) || hasModelsTargetingSessionType(languageModelsService, type)) {","+\t\treturn SessionTypeAvailability.Available;","+\t}","+\t// The \"no Auto\" signal comes from the type's contribution, which loads","+\t// asynchronously. While it's missing — e.g. during a window reload before the","+\t// extension host re-registers contributions — we can't conclude the type","+\t// requires explicit models, so stay selectable (the model picker is the","+\t// backstop and shows \"No models available\" for an active session). This also","+\t// keeps harnesses that do support Auto, like the Copilot CLI, from flashing a","+\t// locked state before their contribution loads.","+\tif (!chatSessionsService.getChatSessionContribution(type)) {","+\t\treturn SessionTypeAvailability.Available;","+\t}","+\t// No Auto fallback and no targeted models. Copilot Free / Student users must","+\t// upgrade to unlock such a type (e.g. the cloud delegation agent is a paid","+\t// feature), so they always get the Upgrade affordance.","+\tconst entitlement = chatEntitlementService.entitlement;","+\tconst canUpgrade = entitlement === ChatEntitlement.Free || entitlement === ChatEntitlement.EDU;","+\tif (canUpgrade) {","+\t\treturn SessionTypeAvailability.UpgradeRequired;","+\t}","+\t// On a paid plan only types that genuinely need their own models are unusable","+\t// here. A type that does not require custom models (e.g. the cloud delegation","+\t// agent, which runs remotely without a local model) stays selectable.","+\treturn chatSessionsService.requiresCustomModelsForSessionType(type)","+\t\t? SessionTypeAvailability.NoModels","+\t\t: SessionTypeAvailability.Available;","+}","+","+/**","+ * Whether any currently registered language model targets the given session","+ * type (e.g. a user-configured BYOK model). General-pool models are ignored","+ * since a session type that requires its own models cannot use them.","+ */","+function hasModelsTargetingSessionType(languageModelsService: ILanguageModelsService, type: string): boolean {","+\treturn languageModelsService.getLanguageModelIds().some(id => {","+\t\tconst metadata = languageModelsService.lookupLanguageModel(id);","+\t\treturn !!metadata && hasModelsTargetingSession([{ identifier: id, metadata }], type);","+\t});","+}","+","+/**","+ * The inline description shown for an unavailable session type, or `undefined`","+ * when it is available. Free / Student users get an actionable \"[Upgrade]\"","+ * link; paid users with no models get a plain \"No models available\" note.","+ */","+export function getSessionTypeUnavailableDescription(availability: SessionTypeAvailability): IMarkdownString | undefined {","+\tswitch (availability) {","+\t\tcase SessionTypeAvailability.UpgradeRequired:","+\t\t\treturn new MarkdownString(","+\t\t\t\tlocalize('chat.sessionType.upgradeLink', \"[Upgrade](command:workbench.action.chat.upgradePlan)\"),","+\t\t\t\t{ isTrusted: { enabledCommands: ['workbench.action.chat.upgradePlan'] } }","+\t\t\t);","+\t\tcase SessionTypeAvailability.NoModels:","+\t\t\treturn new MarkdownString(localize('chat.sessionType.noModels', \"No models available\"));","+\t\tdefault:","+\t\t\treturn undefined;","+\t}","+}","+","+/**","+ * The hover shown for an unavailable session type, or `undefined` when it is","+ * available. Free / Student users are prompted to upgrade; paid users with no","+ * models get an explanation with no upgrade link.","+ */","+export function getSessionTypeUnavailableHover(availability: SessionTypeAvailability): IMarkdownString | undefined {","+\tswitch (availability) {","+\t\tcase SessionTypeAvailability.UpgradeRequired: {","+\t\t\tconst hover = new MarkdownString('', { isTrusted: { enabledCommands: ['workbench.action.chat.upgradePlan'] }, supportThemeIcons: true });","+\t\t\thover.appendMarkdown(localize('chat.sessionType.upgradeHover', \"[Upgrade to GitHub Copilot Pro](command:workbench.action.chat.upgradePlan) to use this agent.\"));","+\t\t\treturn hover;","+\t\t}","+\t\tcase SessionTypeAvailability.NoModels:","+\t\t\treturn new MarkdownString(localize('chat.sessionType.noModelsHover', \"No models are available for this agent.\"));","+\t\tdefault:","+\t\t\treturn undefined;","+\t}","+}","+","+/**","+ * Plain-text description for surfaces that cannot render markdown (e.g. the","+ * mobile picker sheet), or `undefined` when the session type is available.","+ */","+export function getSessionTypeUnavailableLabel(availability: SessionTypeAvailability): string | undefined {","+\tswitch (availability) {","+\t\tcase SessionTypeAvailability.UpgradeRequired:","+\t\t\treturn localize('chat.sessionType.upgradeMobile', \"Requires GitHub Copilot Pro\");","+\t\tcase SessionTypeAvailability.NoModels:","+\t\t\treturn localize('chat.sessionType.noModels', \"No models available\");","+\t\tdefault:","+\t\t\treturn undefined;","+\t}","+}"],"additions":148,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/input/delegationSessionPickerActionItem.ts","lines":["@@ -20,6 +20,7 @@ import { ITelemetryService } from '../../../../../../platform/telemetry/common/t"," import { IsSessionsWindowContext } from '../../../../../common/contextkeys.js';"," import { IChatEntitlementService } from '../../../../../services/chat/common/chatEntitlementService.js';"," import { IChatSessionsService } from '../../../common/chatSessionsService.js';","+import { ILanguageModelsService } from '../../../common/languageModels.js';"," import { ACTION_ID_NEW_CHAT } from '../../actions/chatActions.js';"," import { AgentSessionProviders, AgentSessionTarget, getA